 :tx/rationale "BOOTSTRAP-HYPOTHESIS: The deepest problem is the COLD START. At zero knowledge, braid provides zero hypotheses. FEGH needs a connected graph (requires prior observations), auto-connection needs observations to connect, routing needs tasks with dependencies. All require prior knowledge. At zero knowledge, all are inert. But there IS a signal at zero knowledge: the FILE SYSTEM. Directory structure, file sizes, import relationships, naming conventions encode the project architecture before a single line is read. The file system is the FIRST GENERATIVE MODEL. At braid init time, scanning the project file system generates structural hypotheses: 'internal/consistency/ (10 files, 15KB) — likely core domain logic, investigate first.' These are HYPOTHESES (predictions to investigate), not observations (facts to record). They bootstrap the coupled differential equation dK/dt=f(H), dH/dt=-g(K) by providing the initial H>0 that kicks the system off the trivial fixed point. Without bootstrap: system stays at (K=0, H=0) forever. With bootstrap: system converges to (K=1, H=0). The bootstrap is the difference between a dead system and a convergent one. Implementation: generate_bootstrap_hypotheses(project_root) scans directory tree, collects (path, file_count, total_bytes), parses import/dependency edges, ranks by size*centrality, generates top-10 hypotheses with estimated delta-F(S). ~200 LOC. Surfaced in braid status and braid seed as primary guidance, replacing generic braid self-description."
